<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1436,973,1109]" pageId="15" pageNumber="44">
According to 
<bibRefCitation author="Dirsh" box="[307,452,973,1000]" pageId="15" pageNumber="44" pagination="299 - 400" refId="ref11934" refString="Dirsh V. M. (1958) Revision of the group Portheti (Orthoptera: Acridoidea). Eos, Revista espanola de Entomologia, 34, 299 - 400" type="journal article" year="1958">Dirsh (1958)</bibRefCitation>
the main differences of the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dirsh" authorityYear="1958" box="[845,996,974,1000]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphagidae" genus="Lobosceliana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="44" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[845,996,974,1000]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="44">Lobosceliana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are the antenna with a four-segmented flagellum and two medial segments (but see 
<bibRefCitation author="Hemp, C." box="[651,786,1010,1036]" pageId="15" pageNumber="44" pagination="295 - 300" refId="ref12175" refString="Hemp, C. (2013) A new Lobosceliana Dirsh species (Orthoptera: Pamphagidae: Porthetinae) from coastal Tanzania, East Africa. Zootaxa, 3731 (2), 295 - 300. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3731.2.10" type="journal article" year="2013">Hemp 2013</bibRefCitation>
), strongly expanded margins of hind femur with a straight upper margin and strongly serrated lateral expansions of the apical valves of penis. The distinction from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dirsh" authorityYear="1958" class="Insecta" family="Pamphagidae" genus="Xiphoceriana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Orthoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="44" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="44">Xiphoceriana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is not always clear (see above).
</paragraph>
